20Donald%20Trump%20appears%20eager%20to%20try%20to%20avoid%20the%20topic.%3Cp%3ESusan%20Walsh%2FAP%3B%20Chip%20Somodevilla%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20stock%20market%20hasn't%20been%20pricing%20in%20sizable%20volatility%20risk%20with%20the%202024%20Presidential%20election%20only%20months%20away%2C%20Goldman%20says.%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuch%20a%20tight%20race%20could%20mean%20the%20winner%20doesn't%20get%20declared%20for%20days%20after%20voting.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20uncertainty%20could%20stir%20up%20price%20swings%20that%20investors%20aren't%20currently%20prepared%20for%2C%20according%20to%20the%20firm.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upcoming%20Presidential%20election%20poses%20a%20big%20risk%20for%20the%20stock%20market%20if%20the%20winner%20is%20not%20decisive%20and%20the%20results%20are%20drawn%20out%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fgs-stock%3FmiRedirects%3D1%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bank%20said%20in%20a%20note%20on%20Friday%20that%20investors%20are%20underpricing%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20too-close-to-call%20Presidential%20election%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-trump-november-election-abortion-israel-gaza-swing-states-2024-5%5C%22%3Emost%20polls%20between%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20remain%20incredibly%20close%20and%20within%20the%20margin-of-error.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmplifying%20the%20risk%20of%20a%20drawn%20out%20Presidential%20election%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20both%20Trump%20and%20Biden%20have%20wildly%20different%20fiscal%20and%20economic%20agendas%2C%20which%20include%20divergent%20views%20on%20tax%20policies%2C%20government%20spending%2C%20and%20tariffs%20against%20certain%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20different%20agendas%20translate%20into%20different%20investment%20strategies%20to%20be%20implemented%20by%20portfolio%20managers%20across%20Wall%20Street%2C%20and%20if%20the%20ultimate%20winner%20of%20the%20Presidential%20election%20stays%20undecided%20past%20the%20November%205%20election%20date%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20surge%20in%20market%20volatility%20as%20investors%20wait%20to%20determine%20which%20basket%20of%20stocks%20to%20buy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20for%20a%20drawn-out%20election%20in%20November%20will%20be%20determined%20by%20the%20margin%20of%20victory%2C%20as%20only%20a%20slight%20win%20in%20certain%20states%20could%20automatically%20trigger%20a%20recount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%2023%20states%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20swing%20states%20of%20Arizona%2C%20Michigan%2C%20and%20Pennsylvania%20%E2%80%94%20provisions%20exist%20for%20automatic%20or%20mandatory%20recounts%20if%20the%20margin%20between%20the%20top%20two%20candidates%20is%20within%20certain%20parameters%2C%20typically%200.5%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldman%20Sachs'%20strategist%20David%20Kostin%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%2041%20states%20permit%20a%20losing%20candidate%20to%20petition%20for%20a%20recount%20if%20he%20or%20she%20believes%20they%20were%20aggrieved%20on%20an%20account%20of%20fraud%20or%20mistakes%20in%20the%20canvass%20or%20return%20of%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%202020%20election%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20the%20two%20same%20candidates%2C%20combined%20with%20close%20polls%2C%20it's%20not%20a%20stretch%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20winner%20of%20the%20upcoming%20election%20won't%20be%20determined%20on%20election%20night%20but%20will%20rather%20be%20a%20drawn-out%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20the%20big%20risk%20for%20investors.%20It's%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20%3Cem%3Ewho%3C%2Fem%3E%20wins%20the%20election%20that%20matters%2C%20but%20rather%20%3Cem%3Ewhen%3C%2Fem%3E%20they%20win%20the%20election%20that%20matters%20most%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-volatility-risk-impact-presidential-election-trump-biden-winner-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715002728000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6616e1f83f923f7dab066d48%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-volatility-risk-impact-presidential-election-trump-biden-winner-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It's%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20who%20wins%20the%20election%20that%20matters%2C%20but%20rather%20when%20they%20win%20the%20election%20that%20matters%20most%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mfox%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Fox)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-volatility-risk-impact-presidential-election-trump-biden-winner-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20Americans%20are%20feeling%20a%20six-figure%20salary%20can't%20afford%20them%20a%20middle-class%20lifestyle%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221859%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Middle%20class%20family%20income%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5ca5108086291358f0020723%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221239%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20post%20originally%20appeared%20in%20the%20Insider%20Today%20newsletter.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3EYou%20can%20sign%20up%20for%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubscription%2Fnewsletter%2Finsider-today%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20daily%20newsletter%20here%3