s%20(mean%20age%2082.4%3B%2064%25%20women)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20studied%20the%20white%20matter%20structure%20of%20a%20large%20sample%20of%2064%20super-agers%20over%20the%20age%20of%2080%20and%2055%20age-matched%20typical%20older%20adults%20during%205%20years%20with%20yearly%20follow-ups%20showing%20evidence%20of%20slower%20age-related%20changes%20in%20the%20brains%20of%20super-agers%20especially%20in%20protracted%20maturation%20tracts%2C%20indicating%20resistance%20to%20age-related%20changes%20and%20a%20regional%20ageing%20pattern%20in%20line%20with%20the%20last-in-first-out%20hypothesis.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20these%20participants%20was%20asked%20to%20complete%20a%20variety%20of%20tests%2C%20which%20assessed%20their%20memory%2C%20motor%20and%20verbal%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20noted%20that%20while%20%E2%80%9Cmemory%20normally%20declines%20with%20age%2C%20some%20older%20people%20may%20have%20memory%20performance%20similar%20to%20that%20of%20people%2030%20years%20younger.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20stated%20that%20this%20phenomenon%20is%20%E2%80%9Cconceptualised%20as%20super%20ageing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20revealed%2C%20%E2%80%9CSuper-agers%20and%20typical%20older%20adults%20showed%20no%20difference%20in%20global%20white%20matter%20health%20(total%20white%20matter%20volume%2C%20Fazekas%20score%2C%20and%20lesions%20volume)%20cross-sectionally%20or%20longitudinally.%20However%2C%20analyses%20of%20diffusion%20parameters%20revealed%20better%20white%20matter%20microstructure%20in%20super-agers%20than%20in%20typical%20older%20adults.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20also%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CCross-sectional%20differences%20showed%20higher%20fractional%20anisotropy%20(FA)%20in%20super-agers%20mostly%20in%20frontal%20fibres%20and%20lower%20mean%20diffusivity%20(MD)%20in%20most%20white%20matter%20tracts%2C%20expressed%20as%20an%20anteroposterior%20gradient%20with%20greater%20group%20differences%20in%20anterior%20tracts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20further%20noted%20that%20the%20decline%20of%20this%20FA%20progresses%20at%20a%20slower%20rate%20in%20super-agers%20compared%20to%20the%20usual%20aging%20trajectory%20observed%20in%20older%20adults.%20Additionally%2C%20researchers%20found%20that%20the%20white%20matter%20microstructure%20remains%20more%20intact%20in%20super-agers%20than%20in%20their%20typical%20adult%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20claimed%20that%20understanding%20the%20phenotype%20of%20any%20super-ager%20can%20detail%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmechanisms%20of%20protection%20against%20age-related%20memory%20loss%20and%20dementia.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715001900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F6partuj8_old-person-generic_625x300_06_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsuper-agers-whats-so-special-about-these-80-year-olds-with-younger-brains-5601533%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Super-agers%20have%20an%20incredibly%20sharp%20memory%2C%20comparable%20to%20people%2030%20years%20younger%20than%20them%2C%20as%20per%20a%20study%20published%20in%20The%20Journal%20Of%20Neuroscience.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsuper-agers-whats-so-special-about-these-80-year-olds-with-younger-brains-5601533%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsuper-agers-whats-so-special-about-these-80-year-olds-with-younger-brains-5601533%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsuper-agers-whats-so-special-about-these-80-year-olds-with-younger-brains-5601533%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Columbia%20University%20cancels%20main%20graduation%20event%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715001742000%2C%22visual%22%