w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F05%2FChennai-dr-naveen-4-1714627724-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-348781%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Naveen%20prepares%20unique%20fertilisers%20using%20bananas%2C%20fish%2C%20lemons%2C%20drumstick%20leaves%2C%20and%20more.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTake%20one%20kg%20of%20fish%20in%20a%20clean%20plastic%20container%20and%20mix%20it%20with%20one%20kg%20of%20jaggery%2C%20handful%20of%20drumstick%20leaves%2C%20and%20two%20well-ripened%20bananas.%20Close%20the%20lid%20and%20keep%20it%20under%20shade.%20The%20fertiliser%20will%20be%20ready%20to%20use%20after%2021%20to%2027%20days.%20Rich%20in%20nitrogen%2C%20phosphorus%2C%20and%20potassium%2C%20this%20fertiliser%20helps%20boost%20flowering%20and%20fruiting%20in%20plants.%20It%20should%20be%20given%20once%20every%2015%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20control%20pest%20attacks%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20treating%20seeds%20before%20sowing%20reduces%20the%20chances%20of%20pest%20attacks%2C%20Dr%20Naveen%20says%20urban%20gardeners%20can%20spray%20neem%20oil%20on%20leaves%20every%2010%20days%20to%20prevent%20any%20pest%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20store%20seeds%20for%20next%20season%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Naveen%20says%20that%20one%20of%20the%20advantages%20of%20native%20varieties%20over%20genetically%20modified%20and%20hybrid%20seeds%20is%20that%20you%20do%20not%20need%20to%20purchase%20seeds%20every%20year.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20can%20scoop%20out%20seeds%20from%20vegetables%20and%20seeds%20after%20harvesting.%20Store%20them%20in%20a%20glass%20jar%20with%20some%20charcoal%20powder.%20It%20prevents%20seeds%20from%20being%20degenerated%20and%20increases%20their%20shelf%20life%20to%2010%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3