rcent%20cocopeat%2C%205%20percent%20of%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cake)%20powder%2C%20and%205%20percent%20of%20bonemeal%20powder.%20Before%20transferring%20the%20mix%20into%20the%20pot%2C%20place%20a%20thick%20layer%20(4-5%20inches)%20of%20dried%20leaves%20on%20the%20pot%20which%20will%20turn%20into%20compost%20later%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Add%20liquid%20fertiliser%20to%20boost%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20grown%20on%20a%20farm%2C%20trees%20take%20nutrients%20from%20the%20soil%2C%20but%20when%20we%20grow%20them%20in%20pots%2C%20we%20need%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20additional%20nutrients%20regularly%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jayanti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jayanti%E2%80%99s%20techniques%20have%20helped%20her%20get%20sufficient%20fruits%20for%20the%20past%20three%20decades.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347571%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJayanti%E2%80%99s%20techniques%20have%20helped%20her%20get%20sufficient%20fruits%20for%20the%20past%20three%20decades.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20provide%20additional%20nutrients%2C%20take%201%20kg%20mustard%20cake%20and%20250%20grams%20of%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%20%3C%2Fem%3Epowder%20and%20mix%20it%20in%205%20litres%20of%20water.%20Stir%20it%20and%20then%20keep%20it%20under%20shade%20for%20five%20days.%20Mix%201%20litre%20of%20this%20liquid%20fertiliser%20in%2010%20litres%20of%20water%20and%20give%20the%20diluted%20fertiliser%20to%20the%20plant%20every%2015%20days.%20This%20liquid%20fertiliser%20helps%20boost%20the%20flowering%20and%20fruiting%20in%20the%20trees%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Deal%20with%20pests%20early%20on%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanti%20regularly%20sprays%20neem%20oil%20to%20control%20pest%20and%20insect%20attacks.%20%E2%80%9CUsually%2C%20I%20handpick%20bugs%20from%20plants%20and%20remove%20leaves%20where%20they%20lay%20eggs.%20I%20have%20also%20used%20sticky%20fly%20traps%20to%20control%20fruit%20flies%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Know%20when%20to%20prune%20trees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20keep%20getting%20good%20yields%2C%20Jayanti%20advises%20urban%20gardeners%20to%20keep%20pruning%20trees%20every%20two%20to%20three%20years.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20avoid%20pruning%2C%20then%20you%E2%80%99ll%20start%20getting%20fruits%20that%20are%20smaller%20in%20size.%20Pruning%20helps%20maintain%20tree%20size%20and%20maximise%20fruit%20quality%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Provide%20additional%20nutrients%20for%20rootbound%20trees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20three%20to%20four%20years%2C%20urban%20gardeners%20should%20dig%20out%20a%20thick%20layer%20of%20soil%20(say%203-4%20inches)%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20cow%20dung%20compost%2C%20bonemeal%2C%20and%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%3C%2Fem%3E%20powder.%20Place%20a%20thin%20layer%20of%20soil%20above%20this%20and%20then%20water%